The paper deals with the problem of target localization using binary detectors, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of minimum variance unbiased (MVU) estimator, which is a common concept in mathematical statistics (cs.MA) and machine learning (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper provides simulations to validate the proposed estimator, which falls under the category of modeling and simulation (cs.MS).
